@startuml

title Java Maps Hierarchy - Java 21

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam linetype ortho

skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor<<root>> lightgray
  BackgroundColor<<hash>> orange
  BackgroundColor<<sequenced>> gold
  BackgroundColor<<sorted>> plum
  BackgroundColor<<concurrent>> wheat
  BackgroundColor<<special>> palegreen
  BackgroundColor<<legacy>> lightgray
}

interface Map<K,V> <<root>> #technology
interface SequencedMap<K,V> <<sequenced>> #technology
interface SortedMap<K,V> <<sorted>> #technology

Map <|-down- SequencedMap
Map <|-down- ConcurrentMap
SequencedMap <|-down- SortedMap
SortedMap <|-down- NavigableMap

together {
    interface ConcurrentMap<K,V> <<concurrent>> #technology
    interface ConcurrentNavigableMap<K,V> <<concurrent>> #technology
    interface NavigableMap<K,V> <<sorted>> #technology
}

ConcurrentMap <|-right- ConcurrentNavigableMap
NavigableMap <|-right- ConcurrentNavigableMap

ConcurrentMap <|..down. ConcurrentHashMap
ConcurrentNavigableMap <|..down. ConcurrentSkipListMap
Map <|..down. HashMap
SequencedMap <|..down. LinkedHashMap
HashMap<|-left- LinkedHashMap
NavigableMap <|..down. TreeMap
Map <|...down. EnumMap
Map <|...down. WeakHashMap
Map <|...down. IdentityHashMap

together {
  class HashMap<K,V> <<hash>>
  class LinkedHashMap<K,V> <<sequenced>>
  class TreeMap<K,V> <<sorted>>
  class EnumMap<K,V> <<special>>
  class WeakHashMap<K,V> <<special>>
  class IdentityHashMap<K,V> <<special>>
  class ConcurrentHashMap<K,V> <<concurrent>>
  class ConcurrentSkipListMap<K,V> <<concurrent>>
}

ConcurrentHashMap -[hidden]right- ConcurrentSkipListMap
ConcurrentSkipListMap -[hidden]right- TreeMap
TreeMap -[hidden]right- LinkedHashMap
HashMap -[hidden]right- EnumMap
EnumMap -[hidden]right- WeakHashMap
WeakHashMap -[hidden]right- IdentityHashMap


note left of SequencedMap
  <b>Java 21</b>:
  Map with defined encounter order

  Important methods:
  - firstEntry()
  - lastEntry()
  - pollFirstEntry()
  - pollLastEntry()
  - putFirst()
  - putLast()
  - reversed()

  Sequenced views:
  - sequencedKeySet()
  - sequencedValues()
  - sequencedEntrySet()
end note


note right of SortedMap
  Map sorted by keys

  Sorted by natural order

  Important methods:
  - firstKey()
  - lastKey()
  - headMap()
  - tailMap()
  - subMap()
end note

note right of NavigableMap
  SortedMap with navigation methods

  Examples:
  - lowerEntry()
  - floorEntry()
  - ceilingEntry()
  - higherEntry()
  - descendingMap()
end note


note top of ConcurrentNavigableMap
  Concurrent + NavigableMap

  Used for:
  - sorted concurrent maps
  - range queries
  - navigation by keys
end note


note bottom of HashMap
  Common default choice

  Allows:
  - one null key
  - null values

  No guaranteed order
end note


note bottom of LinkedHashMap
  Has defined encounter order

  Usually: insertion order

  Can also support:
  - access order

  Useful for LRU-like caches
end note


note bottom of TreeMap
  Red-Black tree based Map

  Sorted by keys natural order

  Cost O(log n)
end note


note bottom of EnumMap
  Specialized Map for enum keys

  Very compact and fast

  Keys must be from one enum type
end note


note bottom of WeakHashMap
  Entry can disappear when key
  is no longer strongly reachable

  Useful for cache-like structures
end note


note bottom of IdentityHashMap
  Uses reference equality

  Compares keys by ==
  Not by equals()

  Rare special-purpose Map
end note


note bottom of ConcurrentHashMap
  Scalable thread-safe hash Map

  Usually preferred over
  synchronizedMap(new HashMap<>())

end note


note bottom of ConcurrentSkipListMap
  Concurrent sorted Map

  Skip-list based

  Cost expected O(log n)
end note

@enduml